	shorttitle = {Plant uptake of nitrogen from the organic nitrogen fraction of animal manures},
	url = {https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-agricultural-science/article/plant-uptake-of-nitrogen-from-the-organic-nitrogen-fraction-of-animal-manures-a-laboratory-experiment/ED5B0EAF090606E8B18D4D79EA03E17E},
	abstract = {Twenty slurries, 20 farmyard manures (FYM) and 10 poultry manures were chemically analysed to
characterize their nitrogen (N) fractions and to assess their potential organic N supply. The organic
N fraction varied between manure types and represented from 14\% to 99\% of the total N content.
The readily mineralizable N fraction, measured by refluxing with KCl, was largest in the pig FYMs
and broiler litters, but on average only represented 7–8\% of the total N content. A pot experiment
